## Tables DB — rôles et colonnes importantes

| Table | Rôle | Colonnes clés |
|-------|------|---------------|
| `profiles` | Données publiques + prefs + gamification | `id` (→ auth.users), `username`, `default_role`, `default_engine`, `default_language`, `discord_username`, `portfolio_url`, `bio`, `experience`, `avatar_url`, `has_completed_onboarding`, `onboarding_version`, `xp`, `level`, `unlocked_titles`, `current_title`, `role_stats`, `daily_login_streak`, `last_daily_xp_at`, `invitations_sent_count`, `last_chat_email_sent`, `main_role`, `jam_id` |
| `teams` | Annonces d'équipes | `user_id`, `team_name`, `game_name`, `engine`, `language`, `looking_for` (JSON), `discord_link`, `team_vibe`, `experience_required`, `description`, `jam_id`, `jam_start_date`, `jam_end_date`, `expires_at`, `jam_completion_xp_claimed` |
| `team_members` | Membres acceptés | `team_id`, `user_id`, `role` |
| `join_requests` | Candidatures et invitations | `team_id`, `sender_id`, `type` (`application`\|`invitation`), `status` (`pending`\|`accepted`\|`declined`), `target_role`, `message` |
| `availability_posts` | Joueurs disponibles | `user_id`, `availability`, `role`, `experience_level`, `jam_style`, `engine`, `language`, `portfolio_link`, `username`, `bio`, `jam_id`, `expires_at` (+30j auto) |
| `external_jams` | Jams importées itch.io | `itch_id` (unique), `title`, `url`, `thumbnail_url`, `ends_at` |
| `team_messages` | Chat d'équipe | `team_id`, `sender_id`, `content`, `created_at` |
| `notifications` | Notifs in-app | `user_id`, `type`, `message`, `link`, `is_read`, `created_at` |
| `push_subscriptions` | Abonnements Web Push | `user_id`, `endpoint` (unique), `p256dh`, `auth` |
| `user_badges` | Badges débloqués | `user_id`, `badge_id`, `earned_at` — unique `(user_id, badge_id)` |
| `kudos` | Kudos entre coéquipiers | `sender_id`, `receiver_id`, `category` — unique `(sender_id, receiver_id, category)` |

## Triggers DB importants

- `teams_sync_expires_from_jam_end_trg` : `expires_at` ← `jam_end_date` automatiquement
- `profiles_gamification_columns_protect` : bloque la modif de `xp`, `level`, `unlocked_titles`, etc. côté client (SECURITY DEFINER) — mutations via **admin client** obligatoires
- `handle_new_user` : crée un profil à la création d'un utilisateur

